data.title: Enterprise, UT
data.meta_description: In 2022, Enterprise, UT had a population of 1.52k people with a median age of 31.6 and a median household income of $69,083. Between 2021 and 2022 the population of Enterprise, UT grew from 1,516 to 1,519, a 0.198% increase and its median household income grew from $68,828 to $69,083, a 0.37% increase.
data.text:
As of 2022, 100% of Enterprise, UT residents were US citizens, which is higher than the national average of 93.5%. In 2021, the percentage of US citizens in Enterprise, UT was 99.2%, meaning that the rate of citizenship has been increasing.

In 2022, there were NaNy times more White (Non-Hispanic) residents (1.52k people) in Enterprise, UT than any other race or ethnicity. There were 0 White (Hispanic) and 0 Black or African American (Non-Hispanic) residents, the second and third most common ethnic groups.

The most common job groups, by number of people living in Enterprise, UT, are Management Occupations (105 people), Office & Administrative Support Occupations (82 people), and Construction & Extraction Occupations (73 people). This chart illustrates the share breakdown of the primary jobs held by residents of Enterprise, UT.

The most common employment sectors for those who live in Enterprise, UT, are Construction (152 people), Educational Services (58 people), and Health Care & Social Assistance (56 people). This chart shows the share breakdown of the primary industries for residents of Enterprise, UT, though some of these residents may live in Enterprise, UT and work somewhere else. Census data is tagged to a residential address, not a work address.

In 2022, 0.574% of men over 25 years of age had not completed any academic degree (no schooling), while 0.647% of women were in the same situation.

This visualization illustrates the percentage distribution of the population according to the highest educational level reached. You can filter the data by race by using the selector above.

The following chart display owner-occupied housing units distributed between a series of property tax buckets compared to the national averages for each bucket. In Enterprise, UT the largest share of households pay taxes in the $800 - $1,499 range.

In 2022, 87.3% of the housing units in Enterprise, UT were occupied by their owner. This percentage grew from the previous year's rate of 86.6%.

The following chart displays the households in Enterprise, UT distributed between a series of income buckets compared to the national averages for each bucket. The largest share of households have an income in the $75k - $100k range.

In 2022, 65.1% of workers in Enterprise, UT drove alone to work, followed by those who carpooled to work (23%) and those who worked at home (10.4%).

The following chart shows the number of households using each mode of transportation over time, using a logarithmic scale on the y-axis to help better show variations in the smaller means of commuting.

Using averages, employees in Enterprise, UT have a longer commute time (34.5 minutes) than the normal US worker (26.7 minutes). Additionally, 5.39% of the workforce in Enterprise, UT have "super commutes" in excess of 90 minutes.

The following chart displays the households in Enterprise, UT distributed between a series of car ownership buckets compared to the national averages for each bucket. The largest share of households in Enterprise, UT have 2 cars.

3.36% of the population for whom poverty status is determined in Enterprise, UT (51 out of 1.52k people) live below the poverty line, a number that is lower than the national average of 12.5%. The largest demographic living in poverty are Males 35 - 44, followed by Females 55 - 64 and then Males 45 - 54.

The Census Bureau uses a set of money income thresholds that vary by family size and composition to determine who classifies as impoverished. If a family's total income is less than the family's threshold than that family and every individual in it is considered to be living in poverty.

In 2017, California had the highest estimated number of chronically homeless individuals in the nation, at 35,798. New York has the second highest (5,087), followed by Florida (4,915).

In 2022, insured persons according to age ranges were distributed in 36.3% under 18 years, 15.8% between 18 and 34 years, 30% between 35 and 64 years, and 17.9% over 64 years.
